<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880728-0039 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Boeing Co. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> BA EUROP </CO><IN> AIR ARO </IN><TEXT>   Boeing Co.'s Boeing Commercial Airplane division said it is negotiating for the sale of three 767 jetliners to Olympic Airways, Greece's national airline.    The aircraft sell for about $68 million each, giving the order a total value of about $204 million, a spokesman for Seattle-based Boeing said. Olympic would also take option on two additional aircraft.    Olympic currently flies A-310 model jetliners made by Airbus Industrie, a European consortium based in Toulouse, France, a Boeing spokesman said. </TEXT></DOC>